nodes.text: The Dyne 2577 radial sublight engine was a large model of sublight engine manufactured by the Corellian Engineering Corporation. The AA-9 Freighter-Liner produced by Botajef Shipyards was equipped with two Dyne 2577 engines.
The Dyne 2577 radial sublight engine was first mentioned in the "Starship Fact File" department of the 2015 magazine Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon 50, which was written by Tim Veekhoven.
